%% Critical User Journey — DJ Console host (one slide, three phases)
%% Read top-to-bottom: ① load ② subscribe ③ mutate + fan-out
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as Host UI<br/>(Angular)
    participant API as Spring GraphQL
    participant DB as Domain / DB
    participant Live as Live stream<br/>(WebSocket · graphql-ws)

    rect rgb(42, 62, 52)
    note over UI,DB: ① Boot — one HTTP query loads session + setlist
    UI->>API: Query currentMixSession
    API->>DB: Load active MixSession
    DB-->>API: Aggregate (tracks, energy, …)
    API-->>UI: JSON: full deck state
    end

    rect rgb(38, 52, 72)
    note over UI,Live: ② Stay in sync — same fields as the query, no polling
    UI-)Live: Subscribe mixSessionUpdated(id)
    Live--)UI: First event = snapshot (current server state)
    end

    rect rgb(62, 52, 38)
    note over UI,Live: ③ React — write on HTTP, updates also reach subscribers
    UI->>API: Mutation (e.g. crowdCheered)
    API->>DB: Apply event → persist
    DB-->>API: Updated MixSession
    API-->>UI: Mutation response (HTTP)
    API-)Live: Publish same session object
    Live--)UI: Push → UI treats like another snapshot
    end
